est part of the FIR, not a general airspace closure affecting all commercial transit. While eight excepted airports operating under daylight and permission constraints is restrictive, the language \"all airports in the west part... are closed except...\" describes an airport-level restriction rather than the broad commercial flight suspension the rule contemplates.\n\nThe rule distinguishes between \"broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region\" versus partial closures. This appears to be the latter—a significant but geographically and operationally limited restriction rather than the comprehensive closure required.\n\nThe plaintiff hasn't established the two-airport pathway since it requires complete suspension at two listed airports, which the evidence doesn't support. For the major-region pathway, the raw NOTAM language creates reasonable doubt about whether this rises to the level of a \"broad\" closure of a \"major\" airspace region versus a targeted regional airport restriction.\n\nGiven the preponderance standard and the specificity of the rule language, the evidence falls short of demonstrating a qualifying major closure. The raw NOTAM as the authoritative source suggests the proposition hasn't been met.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"text":"Evidence","type":"text"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782824187-8ZuZwjSQsDN3AL5ygKjK","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782824186974,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"message_update"}
