rations restriction closing airports in the west part of the Tehran FIR, with exceptions for 8 airports operating daylight hours under CAA permission. This is distinguishable from a broad airspace closure affecting commercial transit/arrival/departure across a major region. The rule explicitly excludes \"partial closures.\"\n\n**Decision:**\nWhile the evidence proves a timely, Iran-initiated, non-weather regional airport restriction, it does not establish by a preponderance that the restriction meets the rule's \"major closure\" definition—either as a broad airspace-region closure or as complete suspension at 2+ listed airports.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_caa624b72ddd44a0aa844ada","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\""},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782824186974,"responseId":"gen-1782824187-8ZuZwjSQsDN3AL5ygKjK","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
