ity/military context (non-weather), and timing before May 24 deadline\n\n**Key Issue:**\nThe market rule requires either (1) a \"broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region,\" or (2) complete suspension at 2+ listed airports. The raw NOTAM—the best evidence of what Iran actually issued—is an airport-operations restriction closing airports in the west part of the Tehran FIR, with exceptions for 8 airports operating daylight hours under CAA permission. This is distinguishable from a broad airspace closure affecting commercial transit/arrival/departure across a major region. The rule explicitly excludes \"partial closures.\"\n\n**Decision:**\nWhile the evidence proves a timely, Iran-initiated, non-weather regional airport restriction, it does not establish by a preponderance that the restriction meets the rule's \"major closure\" definition—either as a broad airspace-region closure or as complete suspension at 2+ listed airports.\n\n","type":"text"},{"arguments":{"args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The raw NOTAM A1010/26 (ev_2e5195da64cb) is classified as airport-operations, closing airports in the west part of Tehran FIR except 8 daylight/CAA-permission airports, which does not establish a broad commercial airspace-region closure under the market rule. The separate two-airport complete-suspension path is not proven as the record lacks airport-by-airport proof of complete suspension at 2+ listed airports. Under the preponderance standard, plaintiff has not carried the burden on the decisive major-closure element.\"}","tool":"aar_submit_council_vote"},"id":"call_caa624b72ddd44a0aa844ada","name":"mcp","type":"toolCall"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782824187-8ZuZwjSQsDN3AL5ygKjK","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216","role":"assistant","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":178282418697